		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top" id="forumSubject">Exceptional Acts of Kindness<br clear="all" /><script type="text/javascript">document.title = document.title + ": Thread: Exceptional Acts of Kindness";</script>
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Mar 30th 10:36 AM2005 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a href="/forum.html?forum=62&mid=1112196976974658965&post=1"><a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=62&mid=1112196976974658965&num=10&post=1&replyto=1112196976974658965"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a> | <a class="sm" href="/db/journal2.html?user=399528"><img border="0" src="/shared/user_journal.gif" border="0" height="12" width="17" /> User's Journal</a> | <a class=sm href="mailto:Wondroustremor@allakhazam.com"><img src="/shared/mail3.gif" border="0" height="10" width="17" /> Email User</a>  <a name=1112196976974658965></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=399528"><span id=Sage>Wondroustremor</span></a><b><span id=Sage><br>Sage</span></b><br /><img alt="Avatar" height="100" width="85" src="/uf/Wondroustremor/Avatar1.jpg"><br /><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />467 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [4.77]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Wondroustremor&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform" width="100%"><p>This has been inspired by a stupid mistake I made last night, and one person's kind act in response.<br /><br />Last night, I was buying some materials for a crafting experiment that I and a good friend were doing (seeing how much profit could be made from mass-synthing HQable items after buying the components from Auction House rather than spending time farming the materials).&nbsp;&nbsp;I went to buy some materials for 6k, and escaped out of it by accident, rather than buying them.  I got in a huff, and hurriedly went back in (to the wrong item), and bought a stack of lumber (for what I thought was 6k).  I then realised I'd bought lumber worth 1k... wrong item.  I then also realised I'd paid <i>60k</i> for the item- with the lag, I'd put in too many zeroes.  <img border="0" src="/shared/smilies/banghead.gif" /> <br /><br />I checked the list to see who I'd bought the thing from, and sent a <span style="color: green;">{</span>/tell<span style="color: red;">}</span> to the person, thinking I was doing so in vain- and who could blame him/her- it was my own fault that I'd just bought a 1k item for 60k... 59k profit on a stack of lumber!?  What a steal!  To my shock, I received a response, saying that they'd send me some money back.  I replied that, given the circumstances, I'd welcome even 50k back.  I ran to my <span style="color: green;">{</span>Mog House<span style="color: red;">}</span>, and in my <span style="color: green;">{</span>Delivery Box<span style="color: red;">}</span> was... 59k.  <br /><br />So to Yurizoh, <span style="color: green;">{</span>Thank you.<span style="color: red;">}</span>  <img border="0" src="/shared/smilies/bowdown.gif" /> <br /><br />Anyone else have a story of extreme kindness to share?  </p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Wondroustremor<br />Linkshell: BloodTribe (Remora)<br />http://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.xml?46812 <br />No matter how the wind howls, the mountain cannot bow to it.</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8">Posting from Bermuda</td><td align="right" id="fs8" >11 Replies</td></tr></table>
</td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td>

		   <table class="mform2"  border="0" cellpadding="1" cellspacing="0" width="100%">
		   <tr><td class="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform2" valign="top" id="forumSubject">
		   <span class="sm">Posted @ Wed, Mar 30th 12:24 PM2005 </span><span class="notbold">| <span class="sm">IP: Logged</span> | <a class="sm" href="/forum.html?forum=62&mid=1112196976974658965&num=10&post=1&replyto=111220342234557286"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." height="11" width="17" /> Reply to this</a></a>    <a name=111220342234557286></a></small></td></tr>
		   <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform2" ><span class="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=528570"><span id=Scholar>Kyllendare</span></a><b><span id=Scholar><br>Scholar</span></b><br /><img src="/shared/user_star_ico.gif" height="9" width="9" alt="*" /><br />54 posts
		   <br /><nobr><span class="notbold">Score</span>: Good [3.50]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Kyllendare&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>I can't think of one person who's performed an exceptional act of kindness for me, but I can think of all the people in my LS who've gone above and beyond helping me out in the game.  When I had first joined, the LS leader said that there was basically one rule:  Help each other.  And she truly meant it. <br /><br />Examples:<br /><br />A particular truly exceptional act of kindness that I can think of was when one of my LS mates, when I was just new to the LS, asked me if I was doing alright on my spells and if there was any equipment I needed, and I told him that I was fine, and then asked if there was anything he wanted help with (Like I would be able to do much, as I was a lvl 20ish RDM at the time, and he was a lvl 57ish DRK!).  <br /><br />We got to talking, and I asked him if sometime he could help me quest for my RSE, and he said sure.  In the process of the conversation, we got to talking about how it can sometimes be a pain in the rear that you have to hunt down the chests at specific times to get the magical patterns. <br /><br />Thirty minutes later, I get a tell something like:<br /><br />LS Mate- &quot;You're going to really hate me...go check your MH inbox.&quot; <br /><br />Sure enough, he had actually bought me two pieces of my RSE, and when I tried to refuse them and send them back, he simply said that he remembered how tough it was at a low lvl to make gil and to try to find time to do some of the time specific quests, not to mention the help, so this way- I could quest for these pieces whenever I wanted, and when I finally did get the RSE pieces on my own, I could sell the parts he gave me for money for spells. <br /><br />It was such a kind act, and I don't think I'll ever forget it as long as I'm playing FFXI.<br /><br />However, to top it off, as I futher progressed in levels, and in turn helped out other LS members and players when I could, I would find other little surprises in my in box...<br /><br />Like a Dispel Scroll <br /><br />And then there was the day he gave me a scroll of Phalanx.  But with a catch- he said the first time I used it, he had to be there to watch me test it out.  This player (who shall remain nameless because I know he'd get embarressed) is to me kinda like the Patron Saint of Fledgling RDMs. <br /><br />But as I said, this is about everyone in my LS.<br /><br />Like the time they all came out to help me get my Khazam Keys.  <br /><br />Or all the times they've shown up and supported me when I've organized Mission runs.  I truly couldn't have made it to rank 5 without them.<br /><br />And how almost every time, when I finally got to be able to do my RSE quest, they were there to camp keys with me and then later find the treasure boxes whenever they were able. <br /><br />But there's still many other stories I can think of about how helpful my LS has been to me, and even many other players doing things for me just out of the spirit of kindness.  But there's just too many stories to tell. <br /><br />I do have to say, that because of these acts, I think I'm a better, kinder and more consierate player than I would have been otherwise.  Which to me, is much more important than any of the material rewards of the help I was given. <br /><br />So to all of these players (they know who they are!), I salute you! <br /><br /><br /><br /></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Ariaera: 41 RDM/23 BLM/10 THF/7 WAR<br />Remora Server<br />Bastok Rank 5<br />LS: Circle of Nine<br />http://ffxi.allakhazam.com/profile.x